modules.description: This module provides operations for constructing and transforming indexed ranges over sequences like arrays, strings, bytes, and lists, supporting slicing, folding, and splitting intervals based on explicit bounds or predicates. It enables structural decomposition of ranged data through head/tail access, positional truncation, and predicate-driven partitioning, while facilitating conversions between interval representations and standard collections. Typical applications include text analysis, windowed data processing, and algorithms requiring efficient traversal or segmentation of ordered datasets.
